President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate several individuals for various judicial positions. These nominations include Andrew L. Brasher for Circuit Judge on the United States Court of Appeals for the Eleventh Circuit, John P. Cronan for Judge on the United States District Court for the Southern District of New York, William Scott Hardy for Judge on the United States District Court for the Western District of Pennsylvania, John F. Heil III for Judge on the United States District Courts for the Northern, Eastern, and Western Districts of Oklahoma, John C. Hinderaker for Judge on the United States District Court for the District of Arizona, Iris Lan for Judge on the United States District Court for the Southern District of New York, Matthew T. Schelp for Judge on the United States District Court for the Eastern District of Missouri, Carl Ezekiel Ross for Associate Judge on the Superior Court of the District of Columbia, Alina Ionescu Marshall for Judge on the United States Tax Court, and Christian N. Weiler for Judge on the United States Tax Court. Each nominee has a background in law and brings unique experiences and qualifications to their respective positions.